65Ao_NvYrXIRt47kF-vA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Spring Boot Dependencies**\\n\\nI'm looking at the target POM and noticing that `spring-boot-autoconfigure` is not transitive. The jar itself contains Boot autoconfigure annotations and uses method params like GenericApplicationContext. However, I see that `spring-ai-model` doesn't include Boot. So, if I add `org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter`, will it bring along the Boot autoconfiguration? That seems to be worth exploring further, as it might solve my issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing compilation steps**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I should try compiling with only ToolCallingProperties/AutoConfig. If I run `javac -cp lib.jar T.java`, it could fail due to missing annotation types, so I need to test that. If it doesn’t work, I might add dependencies using Maven or maybe switch to Gradle or Coursier instead. I could also use `mvn dependency:copy-dependencies` as a temporary solution to get those missing parts in place.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RzTVCy4m3zyklI8GhJyq6pxk|fc_09975fa5304b889e016a3f2d3cf3d88197aaff2c27464e1821", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\"; cat > Test.java <<'EOF'\nimport org.springframework.ai.model.tool.autoconfigure.ToolCallingProperties;\npublic class Test { public static void main(String[] args) { System.out.println(new ToolCallingProperties().isThrowExceptionOnError()); } }\nEOF\ncurl -sSfL -o lib.jar https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/springframework/ai/spring-ai-autoconfigure-model-tool/2.0.0-RC2/spring-ai-autoconfigure-model-tool-2.0.0-RC2.jar\njavac -cp lib.jar Test.java 2>&1 | head -50", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1263, "output": 995, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42194, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason"